  "text": "In all groups, samples of effluent were used for assessing shedding of heparan sulfate and syndecan-1 (CD-138) as described in detail elsewhere. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Samples (4 mL) were concentrated to 50 mL with 10 kDa cut-off ultrafilters (Millipore, Billerica, MA, USA). Aliquots (20 mL) were used for determining heparan sulfate and syndecan-1. One enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) (Seikagaku Corporation, Tokyo, Japan) was based on two antibodies specific for heparan sulfate-related epitopes, and the other ELISA (Diaclone Research, Besancon, France) employed a solid-phase monoclonal B-B4 antibody and a biotinylated monoclonal B-D 30 antibody raised against syndecan-1. Detection relied on streptavidin-horseradish peroxidase and tetramethylbenzidine as chromogen in both assays.",
